hogsback/hogback
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:1. a long, sharply crested ridge. 2. a similar shape, especially a cloud heralding a northwest storm in the Si mountains.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (chiefly Cant. mountaineers and trampers)
